=Description=

Neal Gorenflo:

"Shareable friend David Bollier was interviewed at the International Commons Conference (ICC) in Berlin two months ago along with a selection of commons leaders. In these just released videos, he and others give their perspective on this nascent global movement. As I noted in my summary of the conference, the ICC was unique in that it was the first time that digital and physical commoners gathered to find common cause.

I love David's modesty. He calls himself a student in the video. That's true, but he's also an inspiring teacher."
(http://www.shareable.net/blog/david-bollier-on-the-global-commons-movement-video)


